title: Cheryl proudly parades baby bump in new video after pregnancy reveal
text:
Cheryl proudly parades baby bump in new video after pregnancy reveal Cheryl proudly parades baby bump in new video after pregnancy reveal NOW that Cheryl has officially confirmed her pregnancy, she can't get enough of flaunting her bump. / Published 23rd February 2017 
Cheryl unveiled her blossoming bump after months of staying quiet in a new L'Oreal and Prince's Trust campaign. 
Along with stars including Helen Mirren and Katie Piper, the 33-year-old posed for a new ad while showcasing her stomach in a figure-hugging dress. 
And now, a video has emerged showing Cheryl parading her pregnancy curves for all to see. 
PRINCE'S TRUST/L'OREAL PROUD MAMA: Cheryl looked happy to parade her bump for the camera Cheryl's sexiest pictures A selection of pictures covering the highlights of Cheryl Cole's career. 1 / 93 THE BIG REVEAL: This is the first time Cheryl has acknowledged her bump “What makes us different is what makes us beautiful” Cheryl 
The official video for the Prince's Trust and L'Oreal Paris All Worth It campaign has been released, and a camera focuses on the Girls Aloud star's tummy, which she is cradling with both hands. 
Cheryl tells the camera: "We're all worth it" while sitting on a chair. 
Helen Mirren says: "Famous words I know, but L'Oreal Paris has always believed that everyone is worth it, whoever you are…" with Louisa Johnson finishing: "And wherever you're from." 
PRINCE'S TRUST/L'OREAL BLOOMING: Cheryl is nearing her due date Cheryl and Liam in pictures Tuesday, 29th November 2016 The speculation around the romance between One Direction's Liam Payne and X Factor judge Cheryl Fernandez-Versini has been huge – now the pair have finally confirmed they are dating we take a look at the pop star couple's relationship in pictures 1 / 22 
L'OREAL INSPIRATIONAL: The campaign aims to build confidence in young people 
Cheryl then seemingly references her beau Liam Payne's debut song with One Direction, saying: "What makes us different is what makes us beautiful." 
The camera zooms out to show Cheryl posing happily with her hand on her hip, proudly displaying her bump in front of a neutral background. 
The ambassadors of the campaign go on to explain that L'Oreal and the Prince's Trust are teaming up to help 10,000 young people with confidence and self-worth building.
